# Claude Code — Built-in Analytics Reference

> A structured reference of what Anthropic natively provides for measuring Claude Code impact at the organization level, including metrics, access paths, and documentation links.

---

## 1. Analytics Dashboard (UI)

The primary no-code interface for org-level visibility.

| Detail | Info |
|---|---|
| **Access URL** | [claude.ai/analytics/claude-code](https://claude.ai/analytics/claude-code) |
| **Who can access** | Team/Enterprise: Owners, Primary Owners, Admins |
| **Official docs** | [Track team usage with analytics](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/analytics) |
| **Help article** | [Claude Code usage analytics](https://support.claude.com/en/articles/12157520-claude-code-usage-analytics) |

### What it shows

#### Usage Metrics (available on Team + Enterprise, no extra setup)

| Metric | What it measures | Unit |
|---|---|---|
| Lines of code accepted | Total lines of AI-generated code incorporated by the team | Lines / day |
| Suggestion accept rate | % of Claude Code suggestions accepted across the org | Percentage |
| Daily active users | Number of developers actively using Claude Code | Users / day |
| Active sessions | Total Claude Code sessions per day | Sessions / day |
| Lines accepted over time | Daily trend of accepted code lines | Time series |
| Per-user breakdown | Individual lines accepted + email, exportable as CSV | Per user / month |

> **Data reset:** Usage metrics reset at the start of each calendar month. Historical data available at daily granularity.

---

#### Contribution Metrics (public beta — requires GitHub integration)

| Metric | What it measures | Level |
|---|---|---|
| PRs merged with Claude Code | PRs where Claude Code was used in the session | Org + User |
| PRs merged without Claude Code | Baseline PRs with no Claude Code activity | Org + User |
| Lines of code committed with Claude Code | Code shipped where Claude Code assisted | Org + User |
| Lines of code committed without Claude Code | Code shipped without AI assistance | Org + User |
| PRs opened per user | Individual PR activity across the team | Per user |

> **How it works:** Contribution metrics correlate Claude Code session activity with GitHub commits and PRs. Requires installing the [Claude GitHub App](https://github.com/apps/claude) on your org's GitHub account.

**Setup steps:**
1. Install the [Claude GitHub App](https://github.com/apps/claude) (GitHub admin required)
2. Go to [Admin Settings > Claude Code](https://claude.ai/admin-settings/claude-code) as Owner
3. Enable "Claude Code analytics"
4. Toggle on "GitHub analytics" and select your GitHub org(s)
5. Allow up to 24 hours for data to appear

**Important limitations:**
- Requires GitHub Cloud (not GitHub Enterprise Server)
- Not available for orgs with Zero Data Retention enabled
- Not available for Console/API users — Team and Enterprise only

